      <abstract>
        <sec>
          <title>Objective</title>
          <p> Here we present the first video demonstration of reduction corporoplasty in the management of phallic disfigurement in a 17 year old man with a history sickle cell disease and priapism.</p>
        </sec>
        <sec>
          <title>Introduction</title>
          <p> Surgical management of aneurysmal dilation of the corpora has yet to be defined in the literature. Materials and Methods: We preformed bilateral elliptical incisions over the lateral corpora as management of aneurysmal dilation of the corpora to correct phallic disfigurement.</p>
        </sec>
        <sec>
          <title>Results</title>
          <p> The patient tolerated the procedure well and has resolution of his corporal disfigurement.</p>
        </sec>
        <sec>
          <title>Conclusions</title>
          <p> Reduction corporoplasty using bilateral lateral elliptical incisions in the management of aneurysmal dilation of the corpora is a safe an feasible operation in the management of phallic disfigurement.</p>
        </sec>
      </abstract>
